<refnamediv>
<refname>apple_rm</refname>
<refpurpose>Do an apple remove, remove the resource fork as well</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv>
<para><emphasis remap='B'>:BINDIR:/apple_rm</emphasis>
<emphasis remap='I'>FILE</emphasis>...</para>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para><emphasis remap='B'>apple_rm</emphasis>
is a perl script that removes FILE(s) as well as the .AppleDouble
resource fork file(s) that corresponds to FILE(s). 
<emphasis remap='B'>apple_rm</emphasis>
does not delete directories.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>EXAMPLES</title>
<para><emphasis remap='B'>:BINDIR:/apple_rm</emphasis>
test.text</para> 

<para><emphasis remap='B'>:BINDIR:/apple_rm</emphasis>
test.text testing.text</para>

</refsect1>

